cs.DS, cs.GT, cs.CC, cs.CG, cs.DM 

The paper deals with the computational complexity of computing pure Nash equilibria for a new class of strategic games called integer programming games. This involves the study of generating functions for encoding sets of integer points, which falls under the category of computational geometry (cs.CG) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper also uses recent results from the study of short rational generating functions, which is related to computational complexity (cs.CC). The topic of game theory (cs.GT) is also relevant as the paper deals with computing equilibria in strategic games. Finally, the use of algorithms for enumeration and computation suggests that the paper may also fall under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
